uch, this book not only provides a timely analysis of Syria, but also a major and original rethink of the chemical taboo, as well as international norms more widely.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChemical warfarezSyria. 0aChemical weaponsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aChemical weaponszSyriaxHistoryy21st century. 4aPolitical Studies 2021. 4aSecurity, Conflict & Peace 2018. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aChemical weapons.  aObama.  aQuentin Skinner.  aStrategic narratives.  aSyria.  aTaboo.  aUS foreign policy.1 aBentley, Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613506340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526135063423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526135063/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles